- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on improving grasping in clutter using an active perception approach. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper involves estimating grasp poses from visual data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve grasp detection. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses deep learning models for grasp detection. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves controlling a robotic arm to perform grasping tasks.
